items.title: What we know about Maduro's capture
items.description: Maduro and his wife were taken from "a house that was more like a fortress", Donald Trump says.

items.title: Swiss open criminal case against managers of ski resort bar after deadly fire
items.description: It comes after a preliminary investigation found the likely cause was sparklers on champagne bottles being carried too close to the ceiling.

items.title: Craig the beer-ambassador elephant dies aged 54
items.description: The peace-loving pachyderm and lager promoter was an icon of successful conservation, say officials.

items.title: Trump warning over Iran protests 'reckless' says foreign minister
items.description: The US president earlier said if peaceful protesters are killed, Washington "will come to their rescue".

items.title: More than 100 shelter overnight in Japan shrine due to heavy snow
items.description: Visitors of the Mitsumine Shrine spent the night there after roads around it were shut off.
